,"Hessett, Suffolk, England":"英国素福爾可賀瑟特","Rougham, Norfolk, England":"英国諾福爾可盧加姆","lifeSummary":"当John Bacon于1431年出生在英国素福爾可賀瑟特时，他的父亲Stephen Bacon33岁，母亲Margaret De Thorpe30岁。他于1463年与Margery Tillot在英国諾福爾可盧加姆结婚。他们至少是1个儿子的父母。他去世于1513年在他的家乡享年82岁。"},"hr":{"1431–1513":"1431.–1513.","1423–Female":"1423–preminula","1423–Male":"1423–preminuo","1427–Female":"1427–preminula","1429–Male":"1429–preminuo","1431–Female":"1431.–preminula","1435–1497":"1435–1497","1442–Female":"1442–preminula","1476–1547":"1476.–1547","1399–1455":"1399–1455","1401–1443":"1401–1443","11 OCT 1443":"11. listopada 1443.","1547":"1547","1513":"1513.","1435":"1435","1401":"1401","1423":"1423","1455":"1455","1476":"1476.","1443":"1443","1399":"1399","1431":"1431.","1442":"1442","1497":"1497","1463":"1463.","about 1455":"oko 1455.","1429":"1429","1427":"1427","Hessett, Suffolk, England":"Hessett, Suffolk, England","Rougham, Norfolk, England":"Rougham, Norfolk, England"},"cs":{"1431–1513":"1431–1513","1423–Female":"1423–Zesnulá","1423–Male":"1423–Zesnulý","1427–Female":"1427–Zesnulá","1429–Male":"1429–Zesnulý","1431–Female":"1431–Zesnulá","1435–1497":"1435–1497","1442–Female":"1442–Zesnulá","1476–1547":"1476–1547","1399–1455":"1399–1455","1401–1443":"1401–1443","11 OCT 1443":"11. října 1443","1547":"1547","1513":"1513","1435":"1435","1401":"1401","1423":"1423","1455":"1455","1476":"1476","1443":"1443","1399":"1399","1431":"1431","1442":"1442","1497":"1497","1463":"1463","about 1455":"okolo 1455","1429":"1429","1427":"1427","Hessett, Suffolk, England":"Hessett, Suffolk, Anglie","Rougham, Norfolk, England":"Rougham, Norfolk, Anglie"},"da":{"1431–1513":"1431–1513","1423–Female":"1423–Afdød","1423–Male":"1423–Afdød","1427–Female":"1427–Afdød","1429–Male":"1429–Afdød","1431–Female":"1431–Afdød","1435–1497":"1435–1497","1442–Female":"1442–Afdød","1476–1547":"1476–1547","1399–1455":"1399–1455","1401–1443":"1401–1443","11 OCT 1443":"11. oktober 1443","1547":"1547","1513":"1513","1435":"1435","1401":"1401","1423":"1423","1455":"1455","1476":"1476","1443":"1443","1399":"1399","1431":"1431","1442":"1442","1497":"1497","1463":"1463","about 1455":"omkring 1455","1429":"1429","1427":"1427","Hessett, Suffolk, England":"Hessett, Suffolk, England","Rougham, Norfolk, England":"Rougham, Norfolk, England"},"nl":{"1431–1513":"1431–1513","1423–Female":"1423–Overleden","1423–Male":"1423–Overleden","1427–Female":"1427–Overleden","1429–Male":"1429–Overleden","1431–Female":"1431–Overleden","1435–1497":"1435–1497","1442–Female":"1442–Overleden","1476–1547":"1476–1547","1399–1455":"1399–1455","1401–1443":"1401–1443","11 OCT 1443":"11 oktober 1443","1547":"1547","1513":"1513","1435":"1435","1401":"1401","1423":"1423","1455":"1455","1476":"1476","1443":"1443","1399":"1399","1431":"1431","1442":"1442","1497":"1497","1463":"1463","about 1455":"circa 1455","1429":"1429","1427":"1427","Hessett, Suffolk, England":"Hessett, Suffolk, England","Rougham, Norfolk, England":"Rougham, Norfolk, England"},"en":{"1431–1513":"1431–1513","1423–Female":"1423–Deceased","1423–Male":"1423–Deceased","1427–Female":"1427–Deceased","1429–Male":"1429–Deceased","1431–Female":"1431–Deceased","1435–1497":"1435–1497","1442–Female":"1442–Deceased","1476–1547":"1476–1547","1399–1455":"1399–1455","1401–1443":"1401–1443","11 OCT 1443":"11 October 1443","1547":"1547","1513":"1513","1435":"1435","1401":"1401","1423":"1423","1455":"1455","1476":"1476","1443":"1443","1399":"1399","1431":"1431","1442":"1442","1497":"1497","1463":"1463","about 1455":"about 1455","1429":"1429","1427":"1427","Hessett, Suffolk, England":"Hessett, Suffolk, England","Rougham, Norfolk, England":"Rougham, Norfolk, England","nameMeanings":[{"name":"Bacon","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["English (of Norman origin) and French: from the Norman French personal name <i>Bacun</i>, derived from the ancient Germanic name <i>Bac(c)o</i>, <i>Bahho</i>, based on the element <i>bag</i> ‘(to) fight, (to) dispute’. The name was relatively common among the Normans in the form <i>Bacus</i>, of which the oblique case was <i>Bacon</i>.","English and French: from Middle English, Old French <i>bacun</i>, <i>bacon</i> ‘bacon’ (a word of ancient Germanic origin, akin to   Back   3), probably a metonymic occupational name for a preparer and seller of cured pork.","History: Gilles Bacon from Normandy, France, is documented in Quebec City, QC, in 1647. — Michael Bacon from England arrived in Dedham, MA, in 1640. Nathanial Bacon, from Stratton, Cornwall, arrived in Barnstaple, MA, in 1639. Another Nathaniel Bacon (1647–76), from Friston Hall, Suffolk, emigrated to VA and settled at Curl's Neck on the James river."],"variants":[{"name":"Bagg","meanings":["English:","from Middle English <i>bagge</i> ‘bag, pack, bundle’, hence a metonymic occupational name for a maker of bags and sacks of various kinds, including wallets and purses. It might also have been used for a beggar, or for one who carried their belongings in a bag.","from the ancient Germanic personal name <i>Bago</i> (<i>Bac(c)o</i>, <i>Bahho</i>), from the root <i>bag-</i> ‘to fight’ (see   Bacon   2)."]},{"name":"Back","meanings":["English (Devon, Kent, Sussex, and Norfolk): from the Middle English personal name <i>Bakke</i> (Old English <i>Bacca</i>). It is of uncertain origin, but may have been a byname in the same sense as 3.","English: nickname from Middle English <i>bakke</i> ‘bat’, of uncertain application, perhaps a nickname for a person with poor eyesight, from the expression ‘blind as a bat’.","English: from Middle English <i>bakke</i> ‘back’ (Old English <i>bæc</i>), hence a nickname for someone with a hunched back or some other noticeable peculiarity of the back or spine, or a topographic name for someone who lived on a hill or ridge, or at the rear of a settlement."]}]},{"name":"John","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["form of   John  , also used quite frequently in the English-speaking world. In Northern Ireland it is sometimes found as a variant of   Ewan ."],"variants":[]}],"historicEvents":[{"id":1705197,"age":24,"year":"1455","julianDay":2252488,"title":"Wars of the Roses","description":"Wars of the Roses was a series of English civil wars for control of the throne of England between the royal families House of Lancaster and the House of York. The name of the war was derived as the red rose was the symbol of the Lancastrians and the white rose was the symbol of the Yorks.","url":"https://www.history.com/topics/british-history/wars-of-the-roses","urlTitle":"History - Wars of the Roses","jurisdictionLevel":2}],"lifeSummary":"When John Bacon was born in 1431, in Hessett, Suffolk, England, his father, Stephen Bacon, was 33 and his mother, Margaret De Thorpe, was 30. He married Margery Tillot in 1463, in Rougham, Norfolk, England. They were the parents of at least 1 son. He died in 1513, in his hometown, at the age of 82."},"et":{"1431–1513":"1431–1513","1423–Female":"1423–Surnud","1423–Male":"1423–Surnud","1427–Female":"1427–Surnud","1429–Male":"1429–Surnud","1431–Female":"1431–Surnud","1435–1497":"1435–1497","1442–Female":"1442–Surnud","1476–1547":"1476–1547","1399–1455":"1399–1455","1401–1443":"1401–1443","11 OCT 1443":"11. oktoober 1443","1547":"1547","1513":"1513","1435":"1435","1401":"1401","1423":"1423","1455":"1455","1476":"1476","1443":"1443","1399":"1399","1431":"1431","1442":"1442","1497":"1497","1463":"1463","about 1455":"umbes 1455","1429":"1429","1427":"1427","Hessett, Suffolk, England":"Hessett, Suffolk, England","Rougham, Norfolk, England":"Rougham, Norfolk, England"},"fi":{"1431–1513":"1431–1513","1423–Female":"1423–Kuollut","1423–Male":"1423–Kuollut","1427–Female":"1427–Kuollut","1429–Male":"1429–Kuollut","1431–Female":"1431–Kuollut","1435–1497":"1435–1497","1442–Female":"1442–Kuollut","1476–1547":"1476–1547","1399–1455":"1399–1455","1401–1443":"1401–1443","11 OCT